The paper discusses the design and implementation of a new paradigm for cognitive radio systems, which involves the use of full-duplex radios to simultaneously sense and access vacant spectrum. This involves addressing challenges related to protocol design, theoretical analysis, and algorithm development. Given the focus on wireless networks and communication systems, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other relevant sub-categories include cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
